## Description: What is it? (max 1,500 characters)



Design Lens: a tool which helps in the merger of Design Thinking and Biomimicry when developing solutions. Design thinking as about matching people’s needs with a market opportunity. Biomimicry is the interdisciplinary field of creating products by reverse engineering nature. Simply put, it helps researchers study natural phenomena to obtain ideas from nature and apply them to solve real world human problems.  
  
  
Design Lens allows innovators to consider the needs of humans, and learn how nature solves similar needs, and merge these two in creating solutions.

## Purpose: Why do we use this method or tool for R&amp;D? (max 1,500 characters)



To design impactful solutions that consider the needs of both people and planet.

## Summary: Describe in one sentence, what it is and what it does? (max 120 characters)



While Design Thinking emphasizes starting the design process with focus on empathy for human users, and biomimicry extends that concept to include all life forms. The “ideate” step searches nature for inspiration i.e translating strategies by considering nature’s unifying patterns, before implementing it in solutions and inventions.

## Instructions: How is it used for R&amp;D? What steps to follow?



It is used when identifying needs of the end user/market, and when designing solutions to meet that need.
